g.text: Males generally common, spermatheca filled with sperm

g.title: 065->P. goodeyi
g.text: spermatheca filled with sperm, mlateral fields with four inconspicuous lines,
the two outer bands partially areolated,

g.title: 018->P. hexincisus
g.text: Spermatheca reduced, lateral fields with six lines on most of body

g.title: 025->P. scribneri
g.text: labial region slightly offset from body,
tail tapering slightly with smooth terminus

g.title: 027->P. coffeae
g.text: body diam. long with a terminal rudimentary ovary,
female tail tip truncate or hemispherical

g.title: 051->P. vulnus
g.text: labial region almost continuous with body contour,
in a long lobe spermatheca oblong,
post-vulval uterine sac ca 2 vulval body diam. long with rudimentary ovary,
with narrowly rounded to subacute smooth tip

g.text: Female tail tip with a ventral projection

057->P. thornei
g.text: labial region not offset from body,
framework conspicuously extending ca two annuli
into body and 1 annulus into labial region,
the outer ones straight or weakly crenate,

g.title: 059->P. convallariae
g.text: Post-vulval uterine sac longer than 35 μm

g.title: 060->P. penetrans
g.text: pharynx overlapping intestine in a lobe ca 1.5 body diam. long,

g.title: 061->P. pseudopratensis
g.text: female tail tip rounded to truncate,
